      "writtenOn": "2016-11-23T20:54:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The issue I would like to avoid is WriteFn modifying the values returned from IndexValues. Maybe the best solution is to just copy the return value of IndexValues.\n\nI can imagine writing something like this:\n\twriteFn :\u003d func(tx *bolt.Tx, result []boltutil.Record) error {\n\t\ta :\u003d result[0].(*Annotation).Digests[0] \u003d newvalue\n\t}\n\nIf I have implemented IndexValues in the straightforward way:\nfunc (a *Annotation) IndexValues() map[string][]string {\n\treturn map[string][]string{\n\t\tDIGEST_INDEX: a.Digests,\n\t\tTRACE_INDEX: a.Traces,\n\t\tIGNORE_INDEX: a.Ignores,\n\t\tTEST_INDEX: a.TestNames,\n\t}\n}\n\n...then if Store doesn\u0027t copy the results of IndexValues, newvalue will end up in origIndexState.",
      "parentUuid": "50d33c96_ca29c39d",
      "revId": "934d452274e35e40ffc77e3ba16e9b5616afbc99",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
