      "writtenOn": "2016-11-23T02:10:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "nit: The naming and the documentation seem to indicate there is only one type of record being stored in the BoltDB. Is that considered best practice for BoltDB?\n\nIf not, I think it would be useful to adjust the language to make it more intuitive when there are multiple types.\n\nFor example, if I were to use this for Task Scheduler, I would probably do something like:\ntype DB struct {\n  tasks *Store\n  jobs *Store\n}\n\nMaybe s/Store/IndexedBucket/?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "934d452274e35e40ffc77e3ba16e9b5616afbc99",
