        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-23T19:33:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Right now, there is only support for one record type. That\u0027s intentionally, because none the three immediate use cases for this require to store more than one record type. \nI agree that it should support multiple record types. But it would require to add a codec for each type and also specify the record type I am reading/writing with operation. \nI would prefer to add that when we need it. I am happy to help migrate TaskScheduler to this if it makes sense.",
      "parentUuid": "30324888_ea20ef63",
      "revId": "934d452274e35e40ffc77e3ba16e9b5616afbc99",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
