      "writtenOn": "2016-11-23T20:54:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sorry, I don\u0027t think I was very clear. I think the code works as-is for multiple record types (except NewStore), but the naming is a bit confusing. Now is a good time to change the naming. :-)\n\nThe way I would use this for multiple types in the same DB is something like:\ntype DB struct {\n  tasks *boltutil.IndexedBucket\n  jobs *boltutil.IndexedBucket\n}\n\nfunc NewDb(filename string) (*DB, error) {\n  db, _ :\u003d bolt.Open(filename, 0600, nil)\n  tasks, _ :\u003d boltutil.NewIndexedBucket(\u0026boltutil.Config{\n    DB: db,\n    Name: TASK_BUCKET,\n    Indices: TASK_INDICES,\n    Codec: NewTaskCodec(),\n  })\n  jobs, _ :\u003d boltutil.NewIndexedBucket(\u0026boltutil.Config{\n    DB: db,\n    Name: JOB_BUCKET,\n    Indices: JOB_INDICES,\n    Codec: NewJobCodec(),\n  })\n  return \u0026DB{\n    tasks: tasks,\n    jobs: jobs,\n  }\n}",
      "parentUuid": "50d33c96_4a64b3f6",
