      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-11-23T19:33:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s actually fine if an index value contained an IDX_SEPARATOR as long as we are only supporting to lookup by exact value. i.e. if my values is \u0027myvalX\u0027 and \u0027X\u0027 is the IDX_SEPARATOR we will still be able to find \u0027myvalX\u0027 correctly since we would scan the index for \u0027myvalXX\u0027.",
      "parentUuid": "d079ec3f_31c0a836",
      "revId": "934d452274e35e40ffc77e3ba16e9b5616afbc99",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
